    {
      "num": "02 · the move",
      "heading": "Define handoff triggers",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Write down the cases that must leave automation: low confidence, missing policy, angry customer, protected class, regulated advice, payment exception, or repeated failure.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "file": "support/handoff-rules.js",
          "code": "const shouldHandoff =\n  score < 0.72 ||\n  ticket.sentiment === \"angry\" ||\n  risk.includes(\"regulated_advice\") ||\n  attempts > 2;",
          "caption": "A handoff rule is product empathy written as code."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "03 · the check",
      "heading": "Measure graceful exits",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Track not just containment rate, but bad containment. A bot that traps a user in a wrong answer is worse than a bot that quickly brings a person in.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "lab",
